\pard\plain\s21\ql\sb0\sa100\li0\fi0\keep\keepn\b\fs24{}\i{}Oryza\i0{} L.\fs22\b0{}
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}Including \i{}Padia\i0{} Moritzi
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}\b{}Habit, vegetative morphology\b0{}. Annual, or perennial. \b\i{}Culms\i0\b0{} 30–300 cm high; \b\i{}herbaceous\i0\b0{}. Culm nodes glabrous. Leaf blades linear to linear-lanceolate; pseudopetiolate, or not pseudopetiolate. \b\i{}Ligule\i0\b0{} \b\i{}an unfringed membrane\i0\b0{}.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}\b{}Inflorescence\b0{}. Plants bisexual, with bisexual spikelets. \b\i{}Inflorescence\i0\b0{} \b\i{}paniculate (axes usually wavy, the spikelets appressed), or of spicate main branches (the primary branches often reduced to racemes)\i0\b0{}; open; not comprising ‘partial inflorescences’ and foliar organs. Spikelet-bearing axes persistent. Spikelets not secund.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}\b{}Female-fertile spikelets, florets, fruit\b0{}. Spikelets 4–12 mm long; strongly compressed laterally; disarticulating above the glumes (i.e. above the pedicel cup representing them). Rachilla terminated by a female-fertile floret. Hairy callus absent. \b\i{}Glumes\i0\b0{} \b\i{}present to absent (represented only by a small 2-lobed cupule)\i0\b0{}; if present, two; more or less equal; shorter than the adjacent lemmas; awnless. \b\i{}Upper glume\i0\b0{} \b\i{}0 nerved\i0\b0{}. Spikelets with incomplete florets. The incomplete florets proximal to the female-fertile florets. \b\i{}The proximal incomplete florets\i0\b0{} \b\i{}2 (small, vestigial, no more than half the spikelet length, sometimes only bristles)\i0\b0{}; sterile. The proximal lemmas awnless. \i{}Female-fertile florets\i0{} 1. Lemmas entire; pointed; awnless, or mucronate, or awned. Awns when present, 1; apical; non-geniculate; much shorter than the body of the lemma to much longer than the body of the lemma. Lemmas strongly carinate; 3–9 nerved. Palea present; relatively long (but narrower than the lemma). \i{}Lodicules\i0{} present; membranous (but the membranous flange may be narrow); glabrous. \b\i{}Stamens\i0\b0{} \b\i{}6\i0\b0{}. Ovary glabrous. Stigmas 2. \i{}Fruit\i0{} small, or medium sized, or large. Hilum long-linear.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}\b{}Photosynthetic pathway, leaf blade anatomy\b0{}. C\sub{}3\nosupersub{}; XyMS+. Mesophyll with arm cells; without fusoids. Midrib conspicuous; having complex vascularization. All the vascular bundles accompanied by sclerenchyma.
\par\pard\plain\qj\s22\sb0\sa0\li0\fi340\fs22{}\b{}Taxonomy, distribution\b0{}. Bambusoideae; Oryzodae; Oryzeae. 25 species. Holarctic, Paleotropical, and Neotropical.
